The comet is on a so-called hyperbolic orbit, which takes it out of our system - and clearly of interstellar origin, as the International Astronomical Union (IAU) said. It is also responsible for the naming and categorization of celestial bodies. In honor of its discoverer, the interstellar tail star, which had initially been listed under the catalog number C/2019 Q4, was given the designation 2I/Borisov, the first part of the name indicating that it is the second interstellar object discovered in our solar system.
